1. INTRODUCTION

InnerWave ("App") is operated by Limanex Software.

We respect your privacy and are committed to protecting user information. This Privacy Policy explains how information may be collected, used, processed, and protected when you use the InnerWave application.

By using InnerWave, you agree to the practices described in this Privacy Policy.

2. INFORMATION WE COLLECT

InnerWave does not require account creation and does not collect personal identifying information such as name, address, or phone number.

However, the following types of information may be collected automatically:

• User text inputs submitted to generate AI-based insights
• Basic device information (device model, operating system version)
• Application usage statistics
• Crash reports and performance diagnostics

This information is used strictly to operate and improve the application.

3. AI PROCESSING AND AUTOMATED CONTENT

Some features within InnerWave generate symbolic interpretations, signals, or reflections using artificial intelligence.

User-provided inputs may be securely transmitted to third-party AI processing services (such as Groq API) in order to generate automated responses.

These responses are generated algorithmically and are not reviewed by humans.

InnerWave does not use this data to identify individual users.

4. ANALYTICS

InnerWave may use analytics services such as Firebase Analytics to understand how the application is used.

Analytics data may include:

• Feature usage statistics
• Session duration
• Device performance data
• Crash logs

This information helps improve application stability and user experience.

5. ADVERTISING

The free version of InnerWave may display advertisements provided by third-party advertising networks such as Google AdMob.

These services may collect limited device data (such as advertising identifiers) to deliver and measure advertisements.

InnerWave does not control how third-party advertising partners process data.

6. DATA SECURITY

We implement reasonable security measures designed to protect application data.

However, no method of electronic storage or transmission is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

7. DATA RETENTION

InnerWave does not permanently store user-generated text inputs.

Certain anonymized analytics or diagnostic information may be retained for application improvement purposes.

8. CHILDREN'S PRIVACY

InnerWave is not directed to children under the age of 13.

We do not knowingly collect personal data from children.

9. THIRD-PARTY SERVICES

InnerWave may rely on third-party services including but not limited to:

• Groq AI API (for AI content generation)
• Firebase (analytics and crash reporting)
• Google AdMob (advertising)

Each service operates under its own privacy policies.

10. CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY

We may update this Privacy Policy periodically.

Changes will become effective when posted in the application or on the official website.

Continued use of the app after updates constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.

